'''Harri Johannesdahl''' (born August 22, 1961)  is a Finnish businessman and entrepreneur, who currently serves as the [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] for Coolbrook Ltd.,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.coolbrook.fi/team|title=Coolbrook.fi - Team|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> an engineering company developing [[petrochemical]] technology.<ref name=":1">{{cite web| url = https://www.coolbrook.fi/news | title = coolbrook| work = coolbrook| accessdate = 2017-03-07}}</ref> Coolbrook Ltd announced in February 2017, that the company would receive EUR 3.6 million from [[Tekes (agency)|Tekes]], a [[Finland|Finnish]] funding agency for innovation, for the development of plastic technology innovations using the ethene cracking method.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.coolbrook.fi/news|title=News: Coolbrook receives Tekes Funding|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

Johannesdahl also serves as Business Analyst in Namida Diamond Factory Ltd., a mobile and [[Facebook]] game development firm. The Chairman of the Board of Directors of Coolbrook Ltd. and Namida Diamond Factory Ltd. is [[Ilpo Kuokkanen]].

Johannesdahl has previously worked in management and development positions in [[Finland|Finnish]] [[Internet]] and [[Telecommunication|telecom]] companies, such as [[Sonera]] and Elisa. He also has a solid background as business [[consultant]], specializing in [[Startup company|startup companies]], as an entrepreneur in his own consultancy company Johannesdahl Yhtiöt, founded in 2006. In the late 1990's, Johannesdahl played an active role in both founding and developing the Finnish telecom operator and Internet services company [[Saunalahti|Saunalahti Group]] (previously known as [[Jippii]] Group Ltd. and Saunalahden Serveri). He served as the CEO for the company until 2001.

Johannesdahl is [[Master of Economics|M.Sc. (Econ.)]].

