[[File:Yuri Zisser.jpg|thumb|right|Yuri Zisser in Vitebsk, 2015]] '''Yuri Zisser''' ({{lang-be|Юры Зісер}}, born June 28, 1960) is a [[Belarus]]ian web businessman and blogger. He is the founder and owner of [[TUT.by]],<ref>http://www.tutby.com/about/leaders/</ref> the most visited Belarusian web portal.
==Biography== Yuri Zisser was born in [[Lviv]], [[Ukraine]] and graduated from the North Western Polytechnic Institute in [[Leningrad]]. In 1987 he moved to [[Minsk]], [[Belarus]]. In 1992 he established the company ''Nadezhnye programmy'' ({{lang-ru|УП "Надёжные программы"}}).<ref>http://providers.by/people/yurij-zisser/</ref>
He is author of several books on [[Internet marketing]] and software marketing.
